I don't care about the status of the story, as long as it's *good*. This
was more or less a setup for a JLA arc, and a *bad* one in most
respects, too.

What I don't like is the trend of *ending* miniseries, one-shots and
arcs on a cliff-hanger with no proper conclusion to the story. The
&quot;Outsiders&quot; one-shots worked, they had one &quot;case&quot; in each, with a coda
leading into the main title. This one-shot was *all* setup, heroes
gathering in one place, villains in another, getting ready for a battle,
and then it *ends*.

There's also the complication that this story continuing in JLA until
december, while the Wedding itself coming now.

Pudde.
